collections.name: Hip Hop Cubism 1
collections.description:
Ali Shama, a Bronx native, found his artistic voice at the crossroads of hip-hop culture and graffiti. His unique style, Hip Hop Cubism, blends the raw energy of graffiti with the geometric abstraction of Cubism, creating a fusion of classical techniques and urban expression.

Ali’s work bridges tradition and innovation, reimagining natural forms alongside cityscapes and digital elements. Inspired by Cubist masters, he uses graffiti’s language to explore identity, movement, and culture. With Hip Hop Cubism, Ali challenges perceptions, merging the timeless with the contemporary to reflect the complexity of modern life.
